The paper deals with the efficient representation and sampling of realization spaces of 2D Euclidean Distance Constraint Systems (EDCS) based on 1-dof Henneberg-I graphs. This involves combinatorial characterizations of graphs that have efficient configuration spaces, which suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithms for sampling realizations, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The study of realization spaces and their efficient representations also has connections to graph theory (cs.GT) and statistical mechanics (cs.SD).
